{
  "texts": [
    "Our work compliments the RAG pipeline as we assume access to the gold documents or paragraphs from specialized domains and improve the language model's ability to answer the questions.",
    "Task Generation Task generation is a fastgrowing area of research to adapt large language models to follow instructions (Wang et al., 2023; Taori et al., 2023; Honovich et al., 2023; Köksal et al., 2023; Kang et al., 2023; Liu et al., 2024).",
    "They typically condition a model on a set of seed task demonstrations and generate new synthetic tasks (Wang et al., 2023; Honovich et al., 2023; Kang et al., 2023).",
    "However, task generation conditioned on the user's unannotated text has mostly been ignored.",
    "Additionally, generating tasks with API-based models like GPT is expensive and cannot be used for proprietary or private research data (Köksal et al., 2023)."
  ]
}